  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The original hyperparameters of AbLSTM were used (embedding dimension 64, hidden dimension 64, batch size 128 and learning rate 2 × 10 -3).",
    "The negative log sum loss of the AbLSTM model was used as its humanness or VHH-nativeness scores as done in the original work 37.",
    "Here, 549 antibody therapeutics from the IMGT database 75 were obtained from the BioPhi dataset 36.",
    "This dataset includes 196 fully human therapeutic sequences and 353 therapeutics of non-human origin (mouse, chimeric and humanized).",
    "The AUC of ROC and PR curves are computed to quantify the ability of the models to separate these two groups of sequences."
  ],
